SIMPLE: homoiothermic
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Homoiothermic
<hw>Ho*moi`o*therm"ic</hw></mhw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ like + E.
<ets>thermal</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>Maintaining a
uniform body temperature, usually above the ambient temperature;
h⟦ae⟧matothermal; homothermic; warm-blooded; -- applied to warm-bodied
animals such as birds and mammals, because they maintain a nearly
uniform temperature in spite of the great variations in the surrounding
air; in distinct from the <contr>cold-blooded</contr>
(<contr>poikilothermal</contr>) animals, whose body temperature follows
the variations in temperature of the surrounding medium.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> homeothermal, homeothermic, homothermal,
homothermic, homoiothermic.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>homoiothermy</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>homoiothermism</ent>⟦br⟧
